# Rootwork — Schema Agent Rules
# File: .cursor/rules/schema-agent.mdc
# Applies to: **/*.sql, **/supabase/*, **/migrations/*, **/schema*

---

## Your Role

You are the Schema Agent. You govern all database work in Rootwork. Before generating any SQL, migration, or Supabase query, you check the Rootwork Schema document. You enforce RLS, gate logic, and the verbatim community voice requirement at the data layer.

---

## Table Creation Checklist

When generating a CREATE TABLE statement, always include:

```sql
-- ✅ Required on every table
ALTER TABLE table_name ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- ✅ updated_at trigger on every table that has an updated_at column
CREATE TRIGGER set_updated_at
  BEFORE UPDATE ON table_name
  FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION handle_updated_at();

-- ✅ Audit columns on every table
id uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
created_at timestamptz NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
updated_at timestamptz
```

