## RLS Policy Patterns

### Org members only (most tables)
```sql
-- Read
CREATE POLICY "org_members_read" ON table_name
  FOR SELECT USING (
    org_id IN (
      SELECT org_id FROM org_members WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
    )
  );

-- Write
CREATE POLICY "org_members_write" ON table_name
  FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (
    org_id IN (
      SELECT org_id FROM org_members WHERE user_id = auth.uid()
    )
  );
```

### Server-side write only (claude_interactions, stage_progress)
```sql
-- No direct client writes — service role only
CREATE POLICY "server_write_only" ON stage_progress
  FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (false); -- Client cannot insert
-- Service role key bypasses RLS — server handles writes
```

### Admin only (funding_opportunities)
```sql
CREATE POLICY "admin_read_all" ON funding_opportunities
  FOR SELECT USING (is_active = true);

CREATE POLICY "admin_write" ON funding_opportunities
  FOR ALL USING (auth.jwt() ->> 'role' = 'service_role');
```

