## Gate Enforcement SQL Checks

Use these exact queries in middleware. Do not approximate.

### Hard Stop Gate (Stage 02 → Stage 03)
```sql
SELECT id FROM community_engagements
WHERE org_id = $1
  AND who_was_present IS NOT NULL
  AND who_was_absent IS NOT NULL
  AND why_absent IS NOT NULL
LIMIT 1;
```

### Reconciliation Gate (Stage 02b → Stage 03 unlock)
```sql
SELECT reconciliation_completed_at FROM program_design_reconciliations
WHERE org_id = $1
  AND reconciliation_completed_at IS NOT NULL
LIMIT 1;
```

### Tier Gate (Stage 04)
```sql
SELECT tier FROM organizations
WHERE id = $1
  AND tier IN ('growth', 'enterprise');
```

### Tier Gate (Stage 05)
```sql
SELECT tier FROM organizations
WHERE id = $1
  AND tier = 'enterprise';
```

### Multi-user Gate (below Enterprise)
```sql
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM org_members
WHERE org_id = $1;
-- Reject if count >= 1 and org.tier != 'enterprise'
```

